<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="537" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,260,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Moore" box="[325,486,260,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" refString="Moore, B. P. (1976) A species of Chloromerus (Diptera, Chloropidae) swarming in the Canberra district. Australian entomological magazine, 3 (2), 21 - 22." type="journal article" year="1976">
Moore (
<number box="[419,478,260,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" value="1976.0">1976</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested that species of 
<taxonomicName box="[796,943,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Chloromerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[796,943,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Chloromerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be plant feeders as are many other 
<taxonomicName box="[151,290,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chloropidae</taxonomicName>
. He described swarming of 
<taxonomicName box="[607,754,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Chloromerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,754,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Chloromerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. near 
<emphasis box="[857,981,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">striatifrons</emphasis>
(Becker) at the top of trees in 
<collectingCountry box="[1326,1432,295,320]" name="Australia" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Australia</collectingCountry>
. I observed the swarming of 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker" authorityName="Becker" box="[468,861,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scapularum">
<emphasis box="[468,756,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Platycephala scapularum</emphasis>
(Becker)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[898,1024,332,357]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="537">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
in crowns of trees near an irrigation ditch.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1079,404,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="537" type="etymology">
